104
00:05:40,014 --> 00:05:41,054
In VR instead,

105
00:05:42,115 --> 00:05:49,341
There's like a way larger set of movement that a person do when it's inside these experiences.

106
00:05:49,341 --> 00:05:53,825
People can be standing or moving around.

107
00:05:53,825 --> 00:05:56,227
But most importantly, there is no screen.

108
00:05:56,227 --> 00:06:01,151
The display is attached in your head, and you can literally move your head around.

109
00:06:01,151 --> 00:06:03,393
That plays a big difference in the interactive experience.

110
00:06:04,133 --> 00:06:10,959
And also like you like move your hands for performing certain interactions in

111
00:06:10,959 --> 00:06:14,963
environment around you. So there's a big, big difference in terms of experience

112
00:06:14,963 --> 00:06:22,590
here. So like, like, like what's what's like the real difference? What's really

113
00:06:22,590 --> 00:06:26,614
different about it too, if we think about it, is the motion space that we

114
00:06:26,614 --> 00:06:28,515
allow to the person.

115
00:06:30,067 --> 00:06:33,870
So, like in games, which are interactive experiences,

116
00:06:33,870 --> 00:06:36,393
we have a very small motion space

