00:07:10,473 --> 00:07:14,916
What does VR lies in these pictures like something in the middle so they're

129
00:07:14,916 --> 00:07:19,699
like the movement space is like larger compared to the one of games but you

130
00:07:19,699 --> 00:07:24,522
know is this is this actually like lending itself to the same experiences

131
00:07:24,522 --> 00:07:30,245
like having having having like like the player being able to move more doesn't

132
00:07:30,245 --> 00:07:34,608
mean that we can actually think of those game in VR in the same way in which

133
00:07:34,608 --> 00:07:36,549
within games in the screen.

134
00:07:37,485 --> 00:07:40,668
So the practices and the guidelines are really the same.

135
00:07:40,668 --> 00:07:44,811
VR games tend to be more kinesthetic because of this.

136
00:07:44,811 --> 00:07:49,715
And the fact that we have a larger box

