00:11:20,631 --> 00:11:27,953
So the player is not only just operating those weapons,

206
00:11:27,953 --> 00:11:30,713
but it's also kind of like, as it does that,

207
00:11:30,713 --> 00:11:37,175
it moves in ways, if you design the weapons in a certain way,

208
00:11:37,175 --> 00:11:38,935
you make, the player moves in ways that,

209
00:11:38,935 --> 00:11:40,375
it's kind of like enacting a character,

210
00:11:40,375 --> 00:11:42,976
enacting a certain hero role model.

211
00:11:44,815 --> 00:11:47,798
Which is like an idea akin to this marking that dancers do.

212
00:11:47,798 --> 00:11:50,160
And role-playing, it's fun.

213
00:11:50,160 --> 00:11:53,543
So central to our design process really was like,

214
00:11:53,543 --> 00:11:57,728
how can we make role-playing out of hand movements?

215
00:11:57,728 --> 00:12:01,832
How can we design or think of the way in which the player

216
00:12:01,832 --> 00:12:04,134
moves his hands around those objects in such a way

217
00:12:04,134 --> 00:12:05,736
that that becomes an act of role-playing?

218
00:12:07,097 --> 00:12:09,459
So overall, the picture was something like this.

